=> It is introduced in java 1.8v....
=> It is used to join more than one String with specified delimeter..
=> We can concate prefix and suffix while joining strings using StringJoiner...

StringJoiner sj = new StringJoiner(CharSequence delim);
StringJoiner sj = new StringJoiner(CharSequence delim, CharSequence prefix, CharSequence suffix);

these are two constructor available for StringJoiner..............

Example:
========

package LambdaExpressionDemo;

import java.util.StringJoiner;

public class StringJonierDemo {
	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		StringJoiner sj = new StringJoiner("-");
		
		sj.add("Sonu");
		sj.add("is");
		sj.add("Rajat");
		
		
		System.out.println(sj);
	}

}


